    "faq": {
      "type": "faq-interactive",
      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What makes PHYSIO+® different from other massage chairs on the market?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® features the proprietary ROVO XD Dual Mechanism with six independent rollers — a technology exclusive to World of Comfort. Combined with AI BioSensory Intelligence™ that scans your heart rate, blood oxygen, microcirculation, and fatigue index, it delivers a fully personalized therapeutic massage unlike anything available from competitors. The innovative walking technology, deep tissue arm rollers, and self-adaptive flexible SL-track further set it apart as the most advanced massage chair in Scandinavia.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the AI BioSensory Intelligence™ health detection work?",
            "answer": "<p>Simply place your finger on the built-in sensor, and PHYSIO+®'s AI algorithms analyze five key health indicators: heart rate, blood oxygen levels, microcirculation, heart rate variability, and fatigue index. These metrics are distilled into a personalized health score. The AI then automatically calibrates massage intensity, style, and target areas to perfectly match your body's current needs — ensuring every massage session is optimally therapeutic.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the ROVO XD Dual Mechanism, and why is it superior?",
            "answer": "<p>The ROVO XD Dual Mechanism combines two distinct massage systems working in perfect harmony. The upper XD mechanism moves in multiple dimensions — up/down, left/right, in/out, plus variable speed and rhythm — for a lifelike massage across your entire back. The lower mechanism simultaneously delivers deep, targeted therapy to your glutes and upper hamstrings. Together, they provide six independent rollers covering more surface area with greater precision than any single-mechanism chair.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the walking technology in PHYSIO+®?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+®'s walking technology uses an innovative scissor-action mechanism in the leg area that mimics natural walking motion. It gently stretches the lower back, glutes, hamstrings, and knees — areas typically neglected by conventional massage chairs. With 8 dedicated walking programs, it provides a comprehensive lower-body therapy experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q5": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What are the dimensions and weight limits of PHYSIO+®?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® measures 84 cm × 166 cm × 125 cm when upright and 84 cm × 200 cm × 82 cm when fully reclined. The chair weighs 157 kg. It accommodates users up to 150 kg body weight and up to 210 cm in height. The space-saving technology allows the chair to be placed just 5 cm from the wall while still achieving full recline.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q6": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty and service does PHYSIO+® come with?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® includes a comprehensive 5-year manufacturer warranty covering all parts and labor. We offer free white-glove delivery throughout Scandinavia and the EU, including professional installation and demonstration. Optional premium service agreements (5-year and 10-year) are available for extended coverage. Our expert technicians handle everything — from delivery to setup to ongoing maintenance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q7": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What financing options are available for PHYSIO+®?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer three flexible payment options: full payment with no additional cost, 0% down payment spread over 24 months, or 20% down payment with the remainder over 60 months. All financing is handled through our trusted payment partner with competitive rates. This makes the world's most advanced massage chair accessible to everyone who values their health and wellbeing.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q8": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I try PHYSIO+® before purchasing?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely. We encourage all prospective buyers to visit one of our showrooms across Scandinavia to experience PHYSIO+® firsthand. Our wellness consultants will guide you through a personalized demonstration, including the AI health scan and all massage programs. You can book a private consultation through our website or by calling our showroom directly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q9": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the 2-stage zero gravity recline benefit my health?",
            "answer": "<p>The 2-stage zero gravity recline positions your body in a NASA-inspired posture where your legs are elevated above your heart. This distributes your body weight evenly, reducing spinal pressure by up to 80%. It improves blood circulation, reduces swelling in the legs, and allows the massage rollers to work more effectively against gravity — resulting in a deeper, more therapeutic massage experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q10": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What massage programs and styles does PHYSIO+® offer?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® offers 12 automatic massage programs across three categories: Train, Target, and Recover. Additionally, 6 manual massage styles are available: Kneading, Sync, Vibration, Tapping, Shiatsu, and Acupressure — all fully customizable in intensity and focus area.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q11": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is PHYSIO+® suitable for people with back pain or chronic conditions?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® is specifically designed with therapeutic benefits in mind. The self-adaptive flexible SL-track conforms to your spine's unique curvature, while the 2-stage zero gravity recline reduces spinal pressure by up to 80%. Many users with chronic back pain, sciatica, and muscle tension report significant relief. However, we always recommend consulting your physician before use if you have specific medical conditions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q12": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does PHYSIO+® compare to a professional physiotherapy or spa massage?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® bridges the gap between home comfort and professional-grade therapy. Its ROVO XD Dual Mechanism delivers six-roller coverage that rivals the precision of trained hands, while the AI health detection personalizes every session. The investment pays for itself within months compared to regular physiotherapy or spa visits.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q13": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How much electricity does PHYSIO+® use, and how loud is it during operation?",
            "answer": "<p>PHYSIO+® is engineered for energy efficiency, consuming approximately 300W during operation — comparable to a standard television. A typical 30-minute massage session costs just a few cents in electricity. The chair operates at whisper-quiet noise levels thanks to precision-engineered motors and sound-dampening materials.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q14": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the expected lifespan of PHYSIO+®, and how do I maintain it?",
            "answer": "<p>Built with premium-grade components and motors rated for over 10,000 hours of operation, PHYSIO+® is designed to last 15–20 years with proper care. Maintenance is minimal: wipe the vegan leather surfaces with a warm, damp cloth, avoid direct sunlight exposure, and keep the chair in a dry environment.</p>"
          }
        },
